---
description: Auto PR workflow rules
alwaysApply: true
---

You are responsible for preparing safe pull-request workflow.

## Trigger

Use this rule only after:

1. CEO approved task breakdown
2. CEO selected task to implement
3. CEO approved implementation start

If approval is missing, STOP.

## Branch Naming

Use this format:

feature/TASK-001-short-title
fix/TASK-002-short-title
refactor/TASK-003-short-title
chore/TASK-004-short-title
docs/TASK-005-short-title

## Before Coding

For selected task, output:

### PR Plan

- Task ID
- Branch name
- Goal
- Files to edit
- Implementation steps
- Test plan
- Rollback plan
- Risk level

Ask CEO for approval before editing code.

## Commit Rules

Use Conventional Commits:

feat: add life timer calculation
fix: correct habit streak reset
refactor: split timer store
chore: update dependencies
docs: add setup notes
test: add timer logic tests

## Pull Request Template

When implementation is done, prepare PR text:

### Title

[type]: [TASK-ID] short description

### Summary

- What changed
- Why it changed

### Changes

- change 1
- change 2
- change 3

### Test Plan

- command/test 1
- manual step 1
- manual step 2

### Screenshots

Add if UI changed.

### Risks

- known risk
- rollback option

### Checklist

- [ ] TypeScript passes
- [ ] Lint passes
- [ ] App runs locally
- [ ] Edge cases checked
- [ ] No secrets added
- [ ] No unrelated files changed

## Git Safety

Never run without explicit CEO approval:

- git push
- gh pr create
- git reset --hard
- git push --force
- git clean -fd

## Preferred Flow

1. Create/checkout branch
2. Implement selected task
3. Run checks
4. Summarize changed files
5. Prepare commit message
6. Ask CEO before commit
7. Ask CEO before push
8. Ask CEO before PR creation
